Takeaways from today‚Äôs #BearsCamp:1. This was Trubisky‚Äôs best day. He was consistently on the money - not just throwing catchable balls (one of @PFF‚Äôs biggest gripes) but hitting guys in stride putting the ball exactly where it needs to be. #Bears

2. His velocity and timing were also excellent. I used the word ‚Äúdart‚Äù more than once today because that‚Äôs what he was throwing. The one thing missing: deep balls. He hit downfield passes but very few (if any) 9 routes. Something to watch for tomorrow. #Bears
3. Buster Skrine mighta been the star of the show on defense. He was flying around out there getting to and tipping footballs faster than I remember seeing him in previous days. #Bears

4. Eddie Jackson will be deployed in press man coverage often in Pagano‚Äôs defense and I think he could be a weapon there. He broke up a perfectly thrown ball to A-Rob in the back of the end zone showing physicality that I don‚Äôt know if I‚Äôve seen before from him. #Bears

5. Adam Shaheen looked lost. He got his fair share of reps with the first team O and was deployed in the slot and out wide but he dropped a couple and didn‚Äôt make the most of his opportunity. Confidence in him dropping every day. #Bears
6. Wims Marvin Hall could be considered roster locks at this point. #Bears

7. Another day another dominant performance from Khalil Mack. He didn‚Äôt even play that much but he made his presence felt. The entire front was excellent vs run which is nothing new.That‚Äôs all I got. Again lotta encouraging signs today. #Bears
